    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix RRC initialization on first PHY sync in EPC mode\n\n### Summary\nThe `dl_phy_sync_success()` function in the UE MAC layer incorrectly handled RRC initialization during the first PHY synchronization when operating in EPC mode. Due to a copy-paste error from another context, the function included an erroneous `EPC_MODE_ENABLED` check that prevented proper RRC initialization when the UE was connected to an EPC core.\n\nThis caused UEs to remain in an uninitialized RRC state after successful PHY synchronization, leading to failure in establishing RRC connections and inability to perform attach procedures. The issue was particularly evident in simulation environments where EPC mode was enabled but standalone mode was not.\n\nUsers may observe this issue as:\n- UE stuck in RRC_INACTIVE state indefinitely after cell selection\n- Failure to respond to RRC Connection Setup messages from eNB\n- Assert failures during RRC procedure handling due to uninitialized contexts\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/main_ue.c`: Removed incorrect `!(EPC_MODE_ENABLED)` condition from first_sync check in `dl_phy_sync_success()` function to ensure RRC initialization occurs regardless of core network mode.\n"
}